Mexican Stocks: Cemex, Compartamos, Corp. Geo, Empresas ICA

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-09-23T21:18:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/mexican-stocks-cemex-compartamos-corp-geo-empresas-ica.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:45 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 0.6 percent to 32,588.43.  The Mexican Bolsa is trading at 13.7 times analysts’
earnings estimates, near its lowest valuation since July 2009.
“There’s just a lot of opportunities today to buy companies at
cheap prices,” said Leon Cabrera, trader at Vanguardia Casa de
Bolsa, in a phone interview from Mexico City. “Investors are
taking advantage of yesterday’s sharp sell-off.” The IPC index
lost 4.8 percent yesterday.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, gained 1.9 percent to 4.81 pesos. Shares fell 27
percent this week.  Standard & Poor’s  yesterday placed Cemex’s B
credit rating on review for a possible downgrade as the flagging
global economy curbs cement sales, hurting efforts to trim debt.  Compartamos SAB (COMPARC* MM), the holding company that
controls microlender Banco Compartamos, rose 8.1 percent to
17.92 pesos, to pare its losses for the week to 2.1 percent.  Corporacion GEO SAB (GEOB MM), Mexico’s second-largest
homebuilder, gained 3.7 percent to 20.90 pesos. Shares fell 13
percent for the week.  Empresas ICA SAB (ICA* MM), Mexico’s biggest construction
company, advanced 0.6 percent to 15.96 pesos. ICA fell 12
percent this week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
